This paper deals with privacy and data protection in the context of online advertising, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also describes the use of crowdsourcing and data sharing protocols, which are relevant to social and information retrieval (cs.SI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the accuracy of the approach, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
